step.tex:
\begin{align}
\int x^2\left(1 - \dfrac{1}{x^2}\right)dx &= \int \left(x^2 -\dfrac{x^2}{x^2}\right)dx\\
													&= \int x^2 dx - \int 1\,dx\\
													&=\dfrac{x^3}{3} - x + C
\end{align}\\

\text{Here, C is the constant of integration.}

step.reason:
\text{We have used the fact that }
\int x^n dx= \dfrac{x^{n+1}}{n+1}.\\
\text{Check your calculation if you got something else.}
